for ATLAS 13, CMS EBEB 13, CMS EBEE 13, ATLAS 8, and CMS 8, respectively. The results are, of course, sensitive to the assumption of total uncertainties. As will be discussed, although CMS EBEE 13 and CMS 8 show worst fits, these data do not strongly support a 750 GeV resonance -- various excesses and deficits around 750 GeV are not significantly fitted better with new resonance contributions. However, ATLAS 13 and CMS EBEB 13 data are fitted better with a new resonance at around 750 GeV.
